lowers": 18022, "views": 7409, "likes": 38, "replies": 2, "retweets": 5, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 11, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Refining/products"]}}, {"id": "2072482008408662516", "url": "https://x.com/garquake/status/2072482008408662516", "text": "Great piece with Alex Karp and last 10 seconds on Iran was hmmm #oott as oil continues slide", "time": "00:46", "author": "garquake", "author_name": "Burnsco", "followers": 32104, "views": 6515, "likes": 12, "replies": 2, "retweets": 0, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2072576251693240727", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072576251693240727", "text": "Four Saudi VLCCs have emerged this morning outside the Strait of Hormuz, with their draft indicating they are fully laden. \n\nThree of them briefly turned their AIS on a few days ago in the area of Ras Tanura oil port, before going dark, while the fourth went dark earlier.", "time": "07:00", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 105424, "likes": 286, "replies": 10, "retweets": 41, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 21, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2072582985161838838", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072582985161838838", "text": "And Saudi Aramco is loading more tankers inside the Strait of Hormuz / Persian Gulf. Satellite imagery from earlier today shows 3 tankers taking crude in the Sea Islands at Ras Tanura and the SPMs at Al Juaima'h", "time": "07:27", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 54151, "likes": 255, "replies": 12, "retweets": 55, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 22, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2072585547323760971", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072585547323760971", "text": "@dwallacewells Chinse coal use did not fall last year.\n\nIts use in electricity generation in China dropped, but that was offset by other uses (notably, coal-to-chemicals). Overall, Chinese coal consumption in 2025 was largely flat y-on-y (up ~0.3%).\n\nSome extra context: China consumed ~92.2 EJ of co", "time": "07:37", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 4502, "likes": 65, "replies": 2, "retweets": 14, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 2, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["China demand"]}}, {"id": "2072623278363984005", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072623278363984005", "text": "WTI prompt time-spread flips into contango", "time": "10:07", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 59232, "likes": 155, "replies": 17, "retweets": 14, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 12, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2072642662415438226", "url": "https://x.com/oilin60/status/2072642662415438226", "text": "OIL - CUSHING 5-OH!…. “Book ‘em Danno” Stunning that CL is -$50/bbl off of spot highs, if you going to be wrong you might as well be dead wrong, the SOH long oil narrative ranks right up there with some of the best. #OOTT https://t.co/AWWR1Af9yB", "time": "11:24", "author": "oilin60", "author_name": "60 seconds to know", "followers": 2929, "views": 5254, "likes": 43, "replies": 10, "retweets": 3, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 24, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2072657540010168339", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072657540010168339", "text": "The largest US egg producers conspired to manipulate the benchmark price used by the industry. \n\nAnother reminder that some corners of the physical commodity market remain opaque and are vulnerable to manipulation.\n\nUS DoJ statement (and my highlights): https://t.co/BMSjesrrZv https://t.co/V1hQCWocu", "time": "12:24", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 46426, "likes": 181, "replies": 15, "retweets": 33, "quotes": 10, "bookmarks": 37, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": []}}, {"id": "2072668591103656274", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072668591103656274", "text": "Saudi Arabia is pushing barrels both via the pipeline that bypasses the Strait of Hormuz (and loadings are higher now than a few weeks ago) plus in recent days it has started loading inside the Persian Gulf. The result? Lots of oil (and most of it is fresh loadings, not stocks).", "time": "13:07", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 63629, "likes": 425, "replies": 25, "retweets": 61, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 35, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2072670541018751161", "url": "https://x.com/InfinitusCap/status/2072670541018751161", "text": "Omg \nHOLD ON TO YOUR PANTS \nBecause he was dead wrong on March 9\n-\nCNBC's Jim Cramer has now completely flipped:  \"I am in the $50 to $45 camp!\"\nVideo from CNBC minutes ago\n-\n$CL_F #OOTT #CRUDEOIL #BRENT \n@OilHeadlineNews @JuliOnTwtr https://t.co/DjMHGvxU1I", "time": "13:15", "author": "InfinitusCap", "author_name": "Infinitus Capital", "followers": 5609, "views": 4531, "likes": 9, "replies": 1, "retweets": 2, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 3, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2072674829476446566", "url": "https://x.com/InfinitusCap/status/2072674829476446566", "text": "Jim Cramer (great contra indicator) is UBER bearish on 🛢️ #CRUDEOIL this morning \n-\nON MONDAY MARCH 9, HE WAS UBER BULLISH, CALLING FOR $150-$200, And was dead wrong.  Went straight down from that day.\n-\n$CL_F $67.60s right now \n-\n#OOTT\n@Futures06\n@trenderer798 https://t.co/Bn7ogo9DEa", "time": "13:32", "author": "InfinitusCap", "author_name": "Infinitus Capital", "followers": 5609, "views": 5322, "likes": 8, "replies": 3, "retweets": 2, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 1, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2072695141828002044", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072695141828002044", "text": "So far, it's a rush to export more and more oil.\n\nFor sure, some barrels are coming from inventories. But the export surge is steadily supported by rising wellhead output.\n\nSoon, it would be a battle for market share. At that point, we would know if it turns into a price war.", "time": "14:53", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 75766, "likes": 329, "replies": 49, "retweets": 36, "quotes": 11, "bookmarks": 32, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2072717184384536736", "url": "https://x.com/InfinitusCap/status/2072717184384536736", "text": "#Crudeoil about to go green\n\nJim Cramer was UBER UBER bearish this morning on CNBC, calling for $45-$50 next\n\n$CL_F live quote:  $68.14\n\nWTI was $67.70s during his morning rant \n\n#OOTT #CL_F \n-\n@Energy_Tidbits @EnergyPhilFlynn @Ole_S_Hansen https://t.co/H90N5F4m4j", "time": "16:21", "author": "InfinitusCap", "author_name": "Infinitus Capital", "followers": 5609, "views": 1490, "likes": 3, "replies": 2, "retweets": 0, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 0, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2072727365508038777", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2072727365508038777", "text": "US oil rigs +5 to 445\nBaker Hughes\n#oott", "time": "17:01", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "views": 35632, "likes": 20, "replies": 0, "retweets": 0, "quotes": 5, "bookmarks": 0, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Shale/US production"]}}, {"id": "2072727994469159140", "url": "https://x.com/NoamRaydan/status/2072727994469159140", "text": "Additional VLCCs signaling for Basrah, Iraq: Peru Prosperity IMO 9418066, Suriname Prosperity IMO 9376749, and Dominica Prosperity IMO 9395496. So at least 7 VLCCs linked to Sinokor so far are expected to load in Basrah, based on AIS data. \n#Shipping #OOTT #Iraq https://t.co/ONYwvtB4gn", "time": "17:03", "author": "NoamRaydan", "author_name": "Noam Raydan", "followers": 7546, "views": 47850, "likes": 27, "replies": 1, "retweets": 12, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 3, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iraq"]}}, {"id": "2072747058369376292", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2072747058369376292", "text": "Saudi crude and product exports were around 5.8mbpd in recent days rather than 6.3mbpd reported by some media outlets. The higher figure includes volumes from previously stranded cargos based on sources with knowledge about Saudi oil exports\n#oott", "time": "18:19", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "views": 5517, "likes": 27, "replies": 1, "retweets": 3, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 5, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["OPEC+", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2072757494678753684", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2072757494678753684", "text": "Saudi crude and products exports averaged around 5.8 mb/d, rather than the 6.3 mb/d reported by some, according to sources familiar with the matter. The higher figure includes volumes from previously stranded cargoes. #OOTT #SaudiArabia", "time": "19:01", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 43228, "likes": 128, "replies": 2, "retweets": 27, "quotes": 5, "bookmarks": 4, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["OPEC+", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2072757684928176270", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2072757684928176270", "text": "The narrative of having a “glut” in the market is VERY misleading #OOTT", "time": "19:01", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 7451, "likes": 82, "replies": 3, "retweets": 11, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 1, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2072758583834669552", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2072758583834669552", "text": "Hormuz flows are FAR from being normal #OOTT", "time": "19:05", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 5429, "likes": 59, "replies": 10, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 3, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}], "top_authors_by_tweets": [{"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 31, "views": 140244, "likes": 221}, {"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 7, "views": 409130, "likes": 1696}, {"username": "ZmansEnrgyBrain", "name": "Z4 Energy Research", "followers": 11920, "tweets": 6, "views": 14227, "likes": 99}, {"username": "InfinitusCap", "name": "Infinitus Capital", "followers": 5609, "tweets